Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

There remain commercial options to return to the UK from Uruguay.
If you live in the UK and are currently visiting Uruguay, you’re strongly advised to return now by commercial means. Don’t run the risk of getting stranded.
UK special charter flights will only operate for priority countries where commercial will only operate for priority countries where commercial flights are not possible. You should not assume that these flights will become available in countries where commercial routes are operating. Please do not contact the contracted travel management company if no flight is advertised here.
Most commercial flights have stopped. The remaining commercial option to leave Uruguay is an Amaszonas flight on Saturday 04 April 2020, departing Carrasco Airpot at 16:30 hours and landing at Sao Paulo Guarulhos Airport at 19:00. Connections to Europe (but not London) from Sao Paulo are still possible. Transit passengers cannot spend more than 24 hours in Sao Paolo. There are limited options for final transit from Europe to the UK.
Amaszonas website.
The land border and ferry crossings to Argentina are also closed. British nationals wanting to leave Uruguay should wait until the next commercial flight becomes available.
For updates please see @ukinuruguay and Embajada Británica, Montevideo.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
